===========================================================================
PART 2: RANK ANALYSIS (Approach B)
===========================================================================

Key identity: rank_drop(v) = (n-2) + beta_1(T\v)
  So bad vertices have rank_drop = n-1, good vertices have rank_drop = n-2
  At n=5: bad drop = 4, good drop = 3

Sum of rank drops across all vertices (for beta_1=0 tournaments at n=5):
  sum_drops=15, n_bad=0: 240 tournaments
  sum_drops=16, n_bad=1: 240 tournaments
  sum_drops=17, n_bad=2: 120 tournaments
  sum_drops=18, n_bad=3: 120 tournaments

  Expected: each 2-path (a,b,c) involves 3 vertices.
  If we sum rank_drop(v) over all v, we're counting the rank contribution
  of each 2-path up to 3 times (once for each vertex it touches).

